  "text": "Kubernetes implements API group storage version registration through a multi-layer system coordinating which API versions are used for etcd storage. The system consists of several key components:\n\n## REST Storage Providers\nAll API groups in `pkg/registry/*/rest/storage_*.go` define REST storage providers that implement `NewRESTStorage()` methods. These providers register both v1 and (where applicable) v1beta1 storage versions:\n- **With v1beta1 mapping**: `pkg/registry/admissionregistration/rest/storage_apiserver.go`, `pkg/registry/authentication/rest/storage_authentication.go`, `pkg/registry/resource/rest/storage_resource.go`, and `pkg/registry/storage/rest/storage_storage.go` explicitly define both `v1Storage()` and `v1beta1Storage()` methods\n- **v1 only**: Other storage providers like `pkg/registry/apps/rest/storage_apps.go`, `pkg/registry/batch/rest/storage_batch.go`, `pkg/registry/policy/rest/storage_policy.go`, and `pkg/registry/scheduling/rest/storage_scheduling.go` only define `v1Storage()` methods\n\n## ResourceEncodingConfig Interface\nThe `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/storage/resource_encoding_config.go` file defines the critical ResourceEncodingConfig interface with two key methods:\n1. `StorageEncodingFor(schema.GroupResource)` - Returns which GroupVersion is used to store the resource in etcd\n2. `InMemoryEncodingFor(schema.GroupResource)` - Returns the in-memory representation format\n\nThe `DefaultResourceEncodingConfig` implementation provides the `SetResourceEncoding()` method to explicitly map a GroupResource to a specific storage version. This is where v1beta1 to v1 mappings would be configured.\n\n## Storage Version Manager and Tracking\n`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storageversion/manager.go` defines the Manager interface for tracking which resources need StorageVersion updates. The `ResourceInfo` struct contains:\n- `GroupResource`: The resource being managed\n- `EncodingVersion`: The version used for etcd storage