\n- `DirectlyDecodableVersions`: Versions the converter can handle (including v1beta1 even if not served)\n- `ServedVersions`: Versions actually exposed via the API\n\nThe Manager reconciles storage versions across all API server instances by creating/updating StorageVersion objects in the `internal.apiserver.k8s.io` API group.\n\n## StorageVersion API and Migration Control\n`staging/src/k8s.io/api/apiserverinternal/v1alpha1/types.go` defines the StorageVersion CRD which tracks per-server encoding versions and determines when all servers agree on a common storage version (CommonEncodingVersion field).\n\n`staging/src/k8s.io/api/storagemigration/v1alpha1/types.go` defines StorageVersionMigration resources that coordinate the actual migration of data from one storage version to another when the storage version changes.\n\n## Version Registration Chain\nThe full flow is:\n1. REST Storage Provider (e.g., `pkg/registry/admissionregistration/rest/storage_apiserver.go`) calls both `v1Storage()` and `v1beta1Storage()` to register versions\n2. `DefaultStorageFactory.NewConfig()` in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/storage/storage_factory.go` queries ResourceEncodingConfig via `StorageEncodingFor()` to determine which version is the canonical storage version for etcd\n3. The selected storage version is passed to etcd, while other versions are marked as decodable but not the encoding version\n4. StorageVersion Manager registers these decisions via the StorageVersion CRD\n5. `WithStorageVersionPrecondition()` filter in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/filters/storageversion.go` blocks write operations until all API servers report matching storage versions\n\nThe `MergeResourceEncodingConfigs()` function in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/resourceconfig/helpers.go` merges default ResourceEncodingConfig with specific GroupVersionResource overrides to control which version is used for storage."
}
